✨🤩 artist diary 📔 a note to myself as a kid. 
Everyday there are thousands of little things I could do to keep it going. Since very little, I didn’t have stores around like Michaels or Hobby Lobby, so I would make stuff out of literally nothing. A sea shell picked up from the sea, a wood stick, leaves, a rock lol nature was my free store and inspiration. And as much as I admire an easy access to all of the art supplies, tools and materials right now, I wouldn’t change that childhood experience. That little girl was never bored in her childhood, constantly thinking of ways to express her creativity and make something pretty out of nothing 💩😅 
I look back at that kid and thank her for always sticking with me to these days. Now she can have everything she wants from any art store! ✨📔
🩷💙💚❤️💛🧡 
.
.

Thank you everyone who stuck around for so many years supporting my art journey! I started this page when I was fresh out of college and my first few art pieces that I have sold was acrylic paintings on real leaves. It’s been quite some time since then. I’ve learned other skills, techniques and styles which brought me to Phoenix, AZ and got me into the paper collage with resin combo technique. 🙃 I doubt a lot before starting a new project, but I always tell myself that you can at least try and see how it goes. Who is there to judge you??! So, yeah just go and spend time learning about what feeds your soul, it might be the biggest gift you can do for yourself. 💓
